====Quotations====
*'''2000,''' Gary Nabhan, ''Interspecies relationships affecting endangered species recognized by O’odham and Comcáac cultures,'' in ''Ecological Applications,'' Vol. 10, No. 5
*:The '''Comcáac''' or “Seri,” as they are commonly called in Mexico, number fewer than 600 individuals residing in two permanent villages and several temporary fishing camps on the Sea of Cortez coast of Sonora, Mexico near Tiburón Island, which is alos part of their aboriginal territory.
*'''2003,''' Gary Nabhan, ''Singing the Turtles to Sea: The Comcáac (Seri) Art and Science of Reptiles''
*:Although they do not embrace an agricultural tradition per se, the '''Comcáac''' have likely been moving plants around for many decades.
