*:As a recent (Marc 30, 2000) ''New York Times’'' report reveals, the abundance of the desert remains a present reality to contemporary members of the O’odham, '''Comcaac''' and Yoeme nations who recently made a 250-mile trek through the Sonoran desert along the same routes their ancestors traveled.
*'''2003,''' Gary Nabhan, ''Singing the Turtles to Sea: The Comcáac (Seri) Art and Science of Reptiles''
